Apply the translation to each vertex:
$$
 A(0, 0) &\to A'(0 + 3, 0 + 2) = A'(3, 2) \\
 B(4, 0) &\to B'(4 + 3, 0 + 2) = B'(7, 2) \\
 C(2, 3) &\to C'(2 + 3, 3 + 2) = C'(5, 5)
$$

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.65]
 % Grid
 (-1,-1) grid (9,7);
 (-1,0) – (9,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-1) – (0,7) node[above] {$y$};

 % Original triangle
 ll[AtlasTeal!20] (0,0) – (4,0) – (2,3) – cycle;
 (0,0) – (4,0) – (2,3) – cycle;
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (3pt) node[below left] {$A$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (4,0) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$B$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (2,3) circle (3pt) node[above left] {$C$};

 % Image triangle
 ll[AtlasWarm!20] (3,2) – (7,2) – (5,5) – cycle;
 (3,2) – (7,2) – (5,5) – cycle;
 ll[AtlasWarm] (3,2) circle (3pt) node[below left] {$A'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (7,2) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$B'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (5,5) circle (3pt) node[above right] {$C'$};

 % Dashed translation arrows
 (0,0) – (3,2);
 (4,0) – (7,2);
 (2,3) – (5,5);
tikzpicture
center

The image $\triangle A'B'C'$ has vertices $A'(3, 2)$, $B'(7, 2)$, 
and $C'(5, 5)$.
